com.vogistix.iaf.filters
Interface IFilter

public interface IFilter

Author:
zangelo

Represents a filter interface that all filters in a filter graph must implement.

The methods listed below do not fulfill the contract required by the filter graph. Other methods, which are dynamically constructed and called by the graph's class, must be implemented for each input and output pin on the filter. The syntax is as follows:


For nameless inputs, this signature should take an input buffer (in[]), transform it, and place the output in the the output buffer (out[]). The output will then be passed along to the specified output pins, or all of them if none is specified.

public void __process(byte[] in,int ofs,int size,byte[] out)

For named inputs:

public void __process__name(byte[] in,int ofs,int size,byte[] out)
